<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  GitExtensions.ZimerfeldTree.nuspec
  NuGet package manifest for the ZimerfeldTree GitExtensions plugin.

  This file is read by build.ps1, which:
    1. Increments the <version> tag (major.minor.BUILD)
    2. Updates the matching <Version> in the .csproj
    3. Builds in Release mode
    4. Runs: nuget pack GitExtensions.ZimerfeldTree.nuspec -OutputDirectory <root>

  File paths below are relative to this .nuspec (i.e. src\GitExtensions.ZimerfeldTree\).
  The build script copies the compiled DLL to tools\net9.0-windows\ before packing.
-->
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <!-- ── Identity ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <id>GitExtensions.ZimerfeldTree</id>
    <version>1.0.341</version>
    <title>ZimerfeldTree — Hierarchical Branch Tree for GitExtensions</title>
    <authors>Zimerfeld</authors>
    <owners>Zimerfeld</owners>
    <!-- ── Licensing — per NuGet authoring best practices ────────────── -->
    <!--  https://learn.microsoft.com/pt-br/nuget/create-packages/package-authoring-best-practices#licensing  -->
    <license type="expression">MIT</license>
    <!-- licenseUrl is deprecated but kept for older clients -->
    <licenseUrl>https://licenses.nuget.org/MIT</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <!-- ── Description ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <description>
GitExtensions plugin that displays branches hierarchically in a persistent non-modal
tree window.  Branches separated by '/' are shown as nested folder nodes under three
fixed root sections — LOCAL, REMOTES and TAGS.

Plugin do GitExtensions que exibe branches de forma hierárquica em uma janela de árvore
persistente e não-modal.  Branches separadas por '/' são mostradas como nós de pasta
aninhados sob três seções fixas — LOCAL, REMOTES e TAGS.

Features:
  • Real-time filter across all sections
  • Right-click context menu: Checkout, New branch, Merge, Rebase, Rename, Delete
  • Double-click / Enter to checkout
  • Bold highlight for the currently checked-out branch
  • Working-directory combo populated from GitExtensions history
  • Auto-refresh on checkout and repository switch
  • Status bar: Local N | Remote N | Tags N

Funcionalidades:
  • Filtro em tempo real em todas as seções
  • Menu de contexto (botão direito): Checkout, Nova branch, Mesclar, Rebase, Renomear, Excluir
  • Duplo-clique / Enter para checkout
  • Destaque em negrito para a branch atualmente em uso
  • Combo de diretório de trabalho preenchido a partir do histórico do GitExtensions
  • Atualização automática ao trocar de branch ou de repositório
  • Barra de status: Local N | Remoto N | Tags N

Flexible GitFlow hierarchy:
  Classic GitFlow does not provide for a feature branch as a child of another feature —
  all feature/* branches derive from develop and are siblings. ZimerfeldTree GitFlow instead
  allows a flexible hierarchy where a feature/* can derive either from develop or from another
  feature/* above it. When that happens, finishing a feature must cascade all its changes up to
  the parent feature/* node, successively re-applying "finish feature" until it reaches develop.

Hierarquia flexível do GitFlow:
  O GitFlow clássico não prevê uma branch de feature como filha de outra feature —
  todas as branches feature/* derivam de develop e são irmãs entre si. Já o ZimerfeldTree GitFlow
  permite uma hierarquia flexível onde uma feature/* pode derivar tanto de develop quanto de outra
  feature/* acima dela. Quando isso acontece, finalizar uma feature deve cascatear todas as suas
  mudanças até o nó feature/* pai, reaplicando sucessivamente o "finish feature" até chegar em develop.
    </description>
    <summary>
      Hierarchical branch tree viewer plugin for GitExtensions — groups branches by path
      prefix under LOCAL, REMOTES and TAGS sections with filtering and context menu.
      Plugin visualizador de árvore hierárquica de branches para o GitExtensions — agrupa branches
      por prefixo de caminho sob as seções LOCAL, REMOTES e TAGS, com filtro e menu de contexto.
    </summary>
    <!-- ── Project metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/zimerfeld/ZimerfeldTree</projectUrl>
    <readme>README.md</readme>
    <!-- Embedded package icon shown on nuget.org (128x128 PNG recommended).
         iconUrl is deprecated and no longer displayed by nuget.org. -->
    <icon>icon.png</icon>
    <tags>gitextensions plugin branch tree hierarchy git</tags>
    <copyright>Copyright © 2026 Zimerfeld</copyright>
    <language>pt-BR</language>
    <!-- ── Release notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <releaseNotes>
1.0.18 — Initial public release.
1.0.18 — Primeiro lançamento público.
    </releaseNotes>
    <!-- ── GitExtensions plugin marker ───────────────────────────────────
         The GitExtensions Plugin Manager filters the nuget.org feed to packages
         that DEPEND on GitExtensions.Extensibility — without this the package is
         published but never appears in the in-app Plugin Manager.
         The version is the MINIMUM GitExtensions (Extensibility) required. No 6.x
         Extensibility is published on nuget, so 1.0.0.129 (the highest published
         version <= the installed GitExtensions 6.0.5) keeps it compatible with 6.x.
         Raise this only if the Plugin Manager shows the package as "Not compatible". -->
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="GitExtensions.Extensibility" version="1.0.0.129" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <!-- ── Package contents ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <!--
    File paths are relative to this .nuspec file, which lives in:
      src\GitExtensions.ZimerfeldTree\

    So ..\..\  resolves to the repository root (C:\NUGET\ZimerfeldTree\).

    NuGet tools\ scripts (install.ps1 / uninstall.ps1) are executed automatically
    by Visual Studio's Package Manager Console on Install-Package / Uninstall-Package.
    They also work standalone: cd tools && .\install.ps1
  -->
  <files>
    <!-- Plugin DLL in lib\ ROOT (no framework subfolder) — REQUIRED, and intentional.
         The GitExtensions Plugin Manager only extracts a lib group whose target framework
         is in its moniker list: { net5.0..net10.0, any, netstandard2.0 } (see
         gitextensions.pluginmanager Plugin.cs FrameworkMonikers). A DLL in lib\ root is the
         "any" group → matched. A lib\net9.0-windows\ subfolder is NOT in that list → the DLL
         would NOT be extracted and the plugin would fail to install. So the NU5101 pack
         warning ("place under a framework-specific folder") MUST be ignored here. -->
    <file src="..\..\tools\net9.0-windows\GitExtensions.Plugins.ZimerfeldTree.dll" target="lib\" />
    <!-- Same DLL under tools\ for the legacy Package Manager Console install (install.ps1) -->
    <file src="..\..\tools\net9.0-windows\GitExtensions.Plugins.ZimerfeldTree.dll" target="tools\net9.0-windows\" />
    <!-- Package Manager Console automation scripts -->
    <file src="..\..\tools\install.ps1" target="tools\" />
    <file src="..\..\tools\uninstall.ps1" target="tools\" />
    <!-- License file in the package root (best practice) -->
    <file src="..\..\LICENSE.txt" target="" />
    <!-- README displayed on nuget.org / local NuGet feeds -->
    <file src="..\..\README.md" target="" />
    <file src="..\..\README.pt-BR.md" target="" />
    <file src="..\..\README.en-US.md" target="" />
    <!-- Package icon shown on nuget.org (must match <icon> above) -->
    <file src="Resources\icon-128.png" target="icon.png" />
  </files>
</package>